programme.desc: Based on the beloved, best-selling novel by Alice Sebold and directed by Oscar® winner Peter Jackson (The Lord of the Rings trilogy), the film centers on Susie Salmon (Saoirse Ronan), who was just 14 years-old when she was murdered in December 1973 on her way home from school. Following her death she continues to watch over her earthbound family - while her killer remains at large. Trapped in a wondrous, yet mysterious hereafter, Susie finds she must choose between her desire for vengeance and her yearning to see her loved ones heal and move on. What begins as a shocking homicide unravels into a suspenseful and visually inventive journey through the bonds of memory, love and hope - towards a surprising and emotional reckoning.

programme.title: Wild Mountain Thyme
programme.desc: John Patrick Shanley, who created the classic Moonstruck, brings his sweeping romantic vision to Ireland with Wild Mountain Thyme. The headstrong farmer Rosemary Muldoon (Emily Blunt) has her heart set on winning her neighbor Anthony Reilly's (Jamie Dornan) love. The problem is Anthony seems to have inherited a family curse, and remains oblivious to his beautiful admirer. Stung by his father Tony Reilly's (Christopher Walken) plans to sell the family farm to his American nephew (Jon Hamm), Anthony is jolted into pursuing his dreams in this comedic, moving and wildly romantic tale.

programme.title: Last Chance Harvey
programme.desc: In London for his daughter's wedding, a struggling jingle-writer, Harvey Shine (Dustin Hoffman), misses his plane to New York, and thus loses his job. While drowning his sorrows in the airport pub, Harvey meets Kate (Emma Thompson), a British government worker stuck in an endless cycle of work, phone calls from her mother, and blind dates. A connection forms between the unhappy pair, who soon find themselves falling in love.

programme.title: City by the Sea
programme.desc: Crime drama in which a New York cop is shocked to discover that his son is the prime suspect in a murder case he has been sent to Long Beach to investigate. Having been painfully estranged from his son since he divorced his wife and left for a successful career with the NYPD, the cop struggles with the memories evoked in returning to his family's area.

programme.title: Shaft
programme.desc: An NYPD detective attempts to locate an important eyewitness that has mysteriously gone missing in order to uncover incriminating evidence against a wealthy man who fled the country after committing a racially motivated murder.

programme.title: The 9th Life of Louis Drax
programme.desc: After surviving eight near-death accidents throughout his unlucky life, Louis Drax (Aiden Longworth) plunges off a steep cliff on his ninth birthday. While police investigate the cause of Louis's near-fatal fall and the whereabouts of his violent father, Peter (Aaron Paul), acclaimed neurologist Dr. Allan Pascal (Jamie Dornan) uses unorthodox techniques to try to tap into the boy's unconscious mind and reveal the truth about the events that led to his condition. But as he's drawn deeper and deeper into the mystery of Louis's seeming ability to cheat death, the doctor finds himself falling for Louis's mother, Natalie (Sarah Gadon). As new clues emerge in the case, a shocking revelation changes the fates of Louis Drax and everyone around him.

programme.title: Enchanted Kingdom
programme.desc: This absolutely beautiful documentary on our World, its mystical beauty and miracles including slow motion footage of nature, animals, seasons, new life and daily beauties I've never seen nor imagined existed. The photography is sensational. The animal behaviour shown is incredible, beautiful and humorous. Never been a fan of nature documentaries, this blew me away.

programme.title: Tristan + Isolde
programme.desc: Kevin Reynolds' version of one of Western literature's oldest love stories stars James Franco and Sophia Myles in the titular roles. He is a knight in the service of Lord Marke (Rufus Sewell), who is struggling to unite the tribes of Britain in the Dark Ages. She is an Irish princess, betrothed to Marke; a union arranged to stop the Celtic rebellion. When Tristan and Isolde meet by chance, they fall in love but their emotions threaten the safety of the country.

programme.title: The New Daughter
programme.desc: Thriller starring Kevin Costner and Ivana Baquero. A single father moves his two children to rural South Carolina, only to watch his daughter exhibit increasingly strange behavior.

programme.title: Vanguard
programme.desc: VANGUARD Official Trailer (2020) Jackie Chan vs Lion, Action Movie HD © 2020 - Gravitas Ventures

programme.title: Escape from Pretoria
programme.desc: Thriller. Australian thriller, produced in 2020. Based on the real-life prison break of two political captives, Escape From Pretoria is a race-against-time thriller set in the tumultuous apartheid days of South Africa.

programme.title: Fall
programme.desc: Stranded 2,000 feet at the top of a remote, abandoned radio tower, two expert climbers are put to the ultimate test as they desperately fight to survive the elements, a lack of supplies, and vertigo-inducing heights.

programme.title: In Time
programme.desc: Time is the ultimate currency in a dystopian future in which humans stop aging at 25 - but die in a year unless they get more time. From out of this dark dynamic - where the rich can live forever while the working class dies - emerges hope in the person of Will Salas. Given more than a century by a rich man, Will sets out to destroy the system with help from a greedy tycoon's daughter, a quest that puts him in the crosshairs of a determined time cop. Amanda Seyfried and Justin Timberlake star in this dark tale. Cillian Murphy, Olivia Wilde and Alex Pettyfer co-star. Directed and written by Andrew Niccol.

programme.title: Rango
programme.desc: Animated comedy. Director Gore Verbinski teams up with his Pirates of the Caribbean star Johnny Depp for a clever and funny take on the well-worn western template of the outsider arriving to save a small town in peril. The town in question is the sun-baked Dirt, and Depp voices Rango, the hapless pet chameleon who stumbles into it. Having accidentally slain the eagle that's been terrorising Dirt's motley crew of critter citizens, Rango is taken for an action hero and made sheriff in the hope that he'll also deliver Dirt from the evil gunslinger Rattlesnake Jack (Bill Nighy) and solve the mystery of the town's ever-dwindling water supply. A host of desert animals are brought to vivid life, and the film wittily spoofs the western genre while incorporating homages to numerous cinematic landmarks, from Apocalypse Now to Star Wars. It also prides itself on its own quirkiness, marking it out as one of the more adult-friendly animated blockbusters.

programme.title: The Brothers Grimm
programme.desc: Will and Jake Grimm earn their living by traveling from village to village and vanquishing strange supernatural beasts. At least that's what they trick their clients into thinking. Actually, Will and Jake are con artists who cleverly stage the ghostly attacks and then get paid to make them go away. The scam goes as planned until they arrive at a town that is bordered by an actual enchanted forest. Now, The Grimm Brothers must learn to deal with real magic as they encounter many of the fantastic characters and thrilling situations found in their beloved fairy tales.

programme.title: The Musketeer
programme.desc: Adventure movie. American adventure, produced in 2001. As the swords are drawn and the adrenaline is pumping, D'Artagnan and his Musketeers are ready for battle. Never, of course, have they done it with such dancing grace and acrobatic freedom.

programme.title: Survivor
programme.desc: Milla Jovovich and Pierce Brosnan star in director James McTeigue's thriller. Kate Abbott (Jovovich) is an American diplomatic security officer working at the US embassy in London, where she vets visa applications to prevent potential terrorists from entering the States. But when she flags a suspicious Romanian (Roger Rees) to Bill Talbot (Robert Forster), who's high up in the Foreign Service, he unconvincingly dismisses her apprehension. However, it's clear that Kate's on to something when, shortly after expressing her concerns, she narrowly escapes death in a bomb blast that claims the lives of many of her colleagues. An unexpected turn of events causes the US and UK authorities to believe that Kate is in league with the terrorists, forcing her to go on the run, not only from her home and host governments, but also from a relentless assassin called the Watchmaker (Brosnan). Also starring James D'Arcy, Angela Bassett, Dylan McDermott and Frances de la Tour.

programme.title: American Psycho II: All American Girl
programme.desc: A pretty co-ed comes up with a surefire plan to win a desirable teacher's assistant job: kill everyone in her way! Mila Kunis stars as the homicidal college girl who believes the pile of bodies she leaves behind will be her ticket into the FBI.

programme.title: Sin City
programme.desc: Interweaving multiple storylines from Frank Miller's popular comics, this violent crime noir paints the picture of the ultimate town without pity through the eyes of its roughest characters. Bruce Willis stars as a cop with a bum ticker and a vow to protect a sexy stripper (Jessica Alba); Mickey Rourke as an outcast misanthrope on a mission to avenge the death of his one true love (Jaime King); and Clive Owen as Dwight, the clandestine love of Shellie (Brittany Murphy), who spends his night defending Gail (Rosario Dawson) and her Old Town girls (Devon Aoki and Alexis Bledel) from a tough guy (Benicio Del Toro) with a penchant for violence.

programme.title: The Amityville Horror
programme.desc: One of the most notorious real-life hauntings is brought to terrifying new life in this 2005 remake! The setting of one of the bloodiest mass murders in history, the beautiful Long Island house is bought by the young Lutz family...who soon discover the place is infested by a sinister force that wants them dead. Ryan Reynolds, Melissa George and Philip Baker Hall star.

programme.title: Highlander III: The Sorcerer
programme.desc: Deceived that he had won the Prize, Connor MacLeod awakens from a peaceful life when an entombed immortal magician comes seeking the Highlander.

programme.title: Madly in Love
programme.desc: Drama. Italian drama, produced in 1981. Barnaba, a rude bus driver who enjoys the attention of women, one day meets Principessa Cristina, the princess of a local principality.

programme.title: The New Adventures of Aladdin
programme.desc: On Christmas Eve, Sam and Khalid dress up as Father Christmas to steal all they can from the Galeries Lafayette department store. But when the children insist on Sam telling them a story, he begins by recounting the famous tale of Aladdin. But his own inimitable version of course!

programme.title: Vicky Cristina Barcelona
programme.desc: Woody Allen's Spanish-set romantic comedy stars Rebecca Hall, Scarlett Johansson, Javier Bardem and Penélope Cruz. Christopher Evan Welch narrates the exploits of two American friends, Vicky (Hall) and Cristina (Johansson), who are spending the summer in Barcelona. Vicky is engaged to Doug (Chris Messina), who's back in the States, while Cristina is most definitely single, and adventurous. At an art exhibition, they meet Juan Antonio Gonzalo (Bardem), artist and lothario, who takes a shine to both women, and invites them back to his hometown Oviedo, hoping to be more than just their tour guide. Vicky's initial unease at the jaunt is overruled by Cristina, and the visit sparks a complex romantic entanglement. But the fireworks are truly lit when Gonzalo's unstable wife Maria Elena (Cruz) arrives on the scene... Edited for content.

programme.title: Mansfield Park
programme.desc: Period drama set in the early 1800s, based on the Jane Austen novel. A young girl from a loving but impoverished family is sent to live with her wealthy relatives. Though treated as a social inferior by most of the family, she develops skills as a horsewoman and a writer. Growing up to be a beautiful woman, she has many admirers, but when her kindly cousin is courted by a gold-digger, she realises that it is he whom she loves.

programme.title: Lemony Snicket's A Series of Unfortunate Events
programme.desc: Jim Carrey stars in Brad Silberling's sinister family adventure, which nicely evokes the mildly malevolent Gothic atmosphere of the first three of Lemony Snicket's epic series of novels, which detail the dastardly deeds visited upon a trio of children. Violet (Emily Browning), Klaus (Liam Aiken) and Sunny Baudelaire (played by twins Kara and Shelby Hoffman) are doted upon by their loving parents. But that doesn't last. Barely before the titles are out, a terrible inferno has engulfed the family home, leaving them orphans. Now they must use all their ingenuity to survive the attentions of evil Count Olaf (Carrey), their closest living relative, who will commit whatever crime it takes to get his hands on the youngsters' inheritance. However, no one but the young Baudelaires can see what Olaf is up to. Luckily, they have ingenuity aplenty: Violet is a knowledge-obsessed bookworm, Klaus an inventor of genius and Sunny... well Sunny's very, very good at biting. But will that be enough to thwart Olaf's plans involving poisonous snakes, killer leeches and heavy objects? Also starring Timothy Spall, Billy Connolly and Meryl Streep. With Jude Law as the narrator, and featuring a cameo from Dustin Hoffman.

programme.title: Marry Me, Dude
programme.desc: To avoid deportation, Yassine asks his best friend Fred to marry him.

programme.title: The Fighting Temptations
programme.desc: A New York advertising executive who is about to land a big account, has his life shaken up when it becomes known that he has lied about having a college degree. After being fired, his life is further shaken by his debtors who had counted on paying after landing the account. Having to go on the run, he is called back to his southern town roots, when his great aunt dies. At the reading of the will, he learns he has been asked to assume the mantle of choir director of his great aunt's church and if he can get the choir in the Gospel Explosion in Atlanta, he will inherit stock worth $150,000. Unfortunately the choir leaves a lot to be desired and he has to start recruiting. Among others, he gets three prisoners to join. More importantly, he gets a "sinner" from one of the local night clubs to join. While initially scorned and resisted, nonetheless her voice wins everyone but the hardcore church busybody.

programme.title: Happy-Go-Lucky
programme.desc: Mike Leigh's Oscar-nominated comedy-drama stars Sally Hawkins as Poppy, a perpetually optimistic primary school teacher. After introducing her friends, and setting up Poppy's character, Leigh moves the plot along with the introduction of Scott (Eddie Marsan), Poppy's misanthropic driving instructor, who is her exact opposite. As her lessons progress, in tandem with a tentative romance, the relationship between the pair develops.

programme.title: School for Scoundrels
programme.desc: A miserable New York parking attendant decides to enroll in a confidence-boosting course in an effort to impress his dream girl; the scheming teacher of the class, however, begins to develop a romantic interest in the same young woman.

programme.title: Waiting...
programme.desc: A waiter for four years since high school, Dean has never questioned his job at ShenaniganZ. But when he learns that Chett, a high school classmate, now has a lucrative career in electrical engineering, he's thrown into turmoil about his dead-end life. Dean's friend Monty is in exactly the same boat, but he couldn't care less. More concerned with partying and getting laid, Monty is put in charge of training Mitch, a shy new employee. Over the course of one chaotic shift, Mitch gets to know the rest of Shenanigan's quirky staff: Monty's tough-talking ex-girlfriend, Serena, ShenaniganZ over-zealous manager, Dan, and head cook Raddimus, who's obsessed with a senseless staff-wide competition known only as "The Game".

programme.title: The Nanny Diaries
programme.desc: Charming comedy-drama starring Scarlett Johansson, Laura Linney, Alicia Keys, Chris Evans and Paul Giamatti. Annie (Johansson) has just finished college, qualifying with a degree in anthropology and child development. But, quite frankly, she hasn't got a clue what she wants to do next. Fortunately, fate decides to intervene. While sitting in Central Park one day pondering her future, Annie notices a five-year-old boy (Nicholas Art) about to be hit by a car and intervenes to save his life. This, of course, is much to the relief of the boy's mother, Mrs X (Linney), who frantically thanks Annie. Upon asking her name, Mrs X hears "Nanny" instead of 'Annie'. Apparently, not letting the kid be squashed by a vehicle and having the name Nanny is enough for Mrs X to think that Annie would make a great caregiver to her offspring, and hires her as a nanny on the spot. Nothing so much as a National Insurance number or CRB check in sight. Anyway, it transpires that Mrs X and her husband (Giamatti) are wealthy, hyper-busy professionals living on New York City's swanky Upper East Side, so it's a pretty cushy gig. Temporary career secured, Annie sets about her new job in the only way she knows how: as an anthropological study. First play on Film4. Edited for content.

programme.title: Two Is a Family
programme.desc: Prantsusmaa / Suurbritannia 2016 komöödia Lavastaja:Hugo Gélin Osades: Omar Sy, Clémence Poésy, Antoine Bertrand Samuel elab kohustuste-ja vastutusvaba elu Lõuna-Prantsusmaa päikselisel merekaldal inimeste keskel, keda ta armastab ja kellega koos töötab, ilma et end väga ära väsitaks.Ühel päeval aga jätab üks Samueli endisi voodikaaslasi tema kätte paarikuuse beebi Gloria - tema tütre! Suutmata lapse eest hoolitseda, otsustab Samuel ta emale tagasi viia ja sõidab ruttu Londonisse lootusega ta üles leida, kuid tulutult.Kaheksa aastat hiljem, kui lahutamatuteks muutunud Samuel ja Gloria elavad Londonis, naaseb Gloria ema oma tütart tagasi nõudma...

Temporary career secured, Annie sets about her new job in the only way she knows how: as an anthropological study. First play on Film4. Edited for content.

programme.title: Two Is a Family
programme.desc: Prantsusmaa / Suurbritannia 2016 komöödia Lavastaja:Hugo Gélin Osades: Omar Sy, Clémence Poésy, Antoine Bertrand Samuel elab kohustuste-ja vastutusvaba elu Lõuna-Prantsusmaa päikselisel merekaldal inimeste keskel, keda ta armastab ja kellega koos töötab, ilma et end väga ära väsitaks.Ühel päeval aga jätab üks Samueli endisi voodikaaslasi tema kätte paarikuuse beebi Gloria - tema tütre! Suutmata lapse eest hoolitseda, otsustab Samuel ta emale tagasi viia ja sõidab ruttu Londonisse lootusega ta üles leida, kuid tulutult.Kaheksa aastat hiljem, kui lahutamatuteks muutunud Samuel ja Gloria elavad Londonis, naaseb Gloria ema oma tütart tagasi nõudma...

programme.title: Rosie
programme.desc: ROSIE tells the story of a mother trying to protect her family after their landlord sells their rented home and they become homeless. Finding a room, even for a night, is a tough job and finding somewhere permanent to live is even harder. Within the confines of their car, Rosie (Sarah Greene), and John Paul (Moe Dunford) strive to maintain a loving home while shielding their young family from the reality of the situation around them. Rosie examines how even in times of crises, the love and strength of a family can endure.

programme.title: Ogre
programme.desc: Terrible events are worrying the inhabitants of the Morvan. Jules, a child who has recently arrived in the village, senses something sinister near his house.

programme.title: Mr. Morgan's Last Love
programme.desc: (2013) 113 mins 12 Michael Caine and Clémence Poésy star in writer-director Sandra Nettlebeck's romantic comedy-drama. Retired philosophy professor Matthew Morgan (Caine) is a non-French-speaking American living in Paris. Recently widowed, he's attempting to come to terms with the loss of his much-loved wife (Jane Alexander), with whom he has fantasy chats. One day, he meets lonely young dance teacher Pauline (Poesy) on a bus, where she helps him out of an awkward situation. It's the start of a relaxed but close friendship that rekindles his dormant interest in life. She teaches him the cha-cha and he talks to her about the great thinkers of philosophy. But his sadness about his bereavement overwhelms him and he attempts to kill himself. Morgan's estranged children, Miles (Justin Kirk) and Karen (Gillian Anderson), turn up from America. They're both worried and angry about their father and his new friendship, not least because they believe Pauline might be a gold-digger. Network premiere.

programme.title: The Butler
programme.desc: The Butler (2013) is an American historical drama directed by Lee Daniels and starring Forest Whitaker and Oprah Winfrey. At the White House an elderly butler named Cecil Gaines is waiting for the newly inaugurated president Barack Obama. While waiting, the butler recounts his life story and all the former US presidents he served. A butler's job requires keeping what you heard to yourself and doing your job unnoticed. Serving eight presidents during his tenure, Cecil observed how American society was changing and even he has felt these changes.

programme.title: Piece Montee / The Wedding Cake
programme.desc: Families gather together for a happy day - the wedding of their children - but it's also the time to reveal all their secrets.

programme.title: Mozart and the Whale
programme.desc: A love story between two savants with Asperger's syndrome, a kind of autism whose effects sabotage their budding relationship.

programme.title: The First Day of the Rest of Your Life
programme.desc: Marie-Jeanne and Robert Duval have three children: Albert, Raphaël and Fleur. The portrait of this family is sketched over a dozen years, but only through five particular days, five decisive days, more important than the others, where nothing will ever be the same the next day...

programme.title: Starving Generation
programme.desc: At the age of 21, Zoe, who has quit her studies, moves into a roommate. After yet another low-paying job, the young woman decides to rebel. She writes a Charter of the hungry, a list of things that young people should no longer accept at work. Her goal is to attack the system from the inside by leading a collective fight, to think bigger, but above all to think together...

programme.title: The Lookout
programme.desc: Daniel Auteuil, Mathieu Kassovitz and Olivier Gourmet star in this French crime drama, in which director Michele Placido spins a swiftly moving, complex tale of intrigue and murderous deception. Parisian chief inspector Mattei (Auteuil) believes his carefully prepared sting will finally net a band of persistent bank robbers. But, just as the police operation is reaching its climax, an unseen sniper starts to pick off Mattei's men and, in the blood-drenched confusion, the thieves escape with their loot. Emerging from the carnage, Mattei vows revenge and soon has the suspected killer, Vincent (Kassovitz), in custody. But as his investigation develops further, it becomes clear that it won't be easy to pin the crime on the young man; and he still needs to track down the rest of the gang. Meanwhile, holed-up in the countryside with a doctor (Gourmet) who has been hired to patch them up, the criminals begin to realise that they're far from safe - and it's not the police that they most have to worry about. In French with English subtitles. Film4 premiere.

programme.title: Synecdoche, New York
programme.desc: Theater director Caden Cotard is mounting a new play. Fresh off of a successful production of Death of a Salesman, he has traded in the suburban blue-hairs and regional theater of Schenectady for the cultured audiences and bright footlights of Broadway. Armed with a MacArthur grant and determined to create a piece of brutal realism and honesty, something into which he can put his whole self, he gathers an ensemble cast into a warehouse in Manhattan's theater district. He directs them in a celebration of the mundane, instructing each to live out their constructed lives in a small mock-up of the city outside. As the city inside the warehouse grows, Caden's own life veers wildly off the tracks. The shadow of his ex-wife Adele, a celebrated painter who left him years ago for Germany's art scene, sneers at him from every corner. Somewhere in Berlin, his daughter Olive is growing up under the questionable guidance of Adele's friend, Maria. He's helplessly driving his marriage to actress ...

programme.title: Food of Love
programme.desc: A group of ex-university students reunite to perform a Shakespeare play in a quaint English village.

programme.title: Heavy Trip
programme.desc: Turo (25) is stuck in a small village in Northern Finland. The only glimpses of light in his life are provided by the amateur metal band, Impaled Rektum, whose vocalist he is. He and his friends have played for 12 years without having a single gig. The guys get a surprise visitor from Norway: the head of Northern Damnation, a huge metal festival. They decide that it's now or never. After a miserable warm-up gig Impaled Rektum breaks up just to get together again. They steal a van, a corpse and a coffin from the local cemetery, a new drummer from the local mental hospital and flee to Norway. As they are escaping Finnish police, they have to face the Norwegian Army and its notorious "Delta troppen" in order to get to play their first real gig.

programme.title: Wildest Survival
programme.desc: Dive into the breathtaking world of nature as we explore the lives of our planet's weirdest and wildest creatures, learning how they have adapted to their surroundings in order to survive. Some of these remarkable species have lived on our planet for thousands, if not millions, of years. We reveal how these animals have evolved through the generations to remain a thriving species. With the current, devastating environmental plight, Wildest Survival showcases the importance of these wonderful species, showing what we could lose if human habits remain unaltered.

programme.title: Wild Dogs: Running with the Pack
programme.desc: Return to South Luangwa to see the new pups born to the mighty Manzi and the tiny-but-fearless Kakumbi packs. See yearling Snowy face a hungry hyena before a lion pride scatters Manzi mum Weka's pups and leaves her frantically searching for them.

programme.title: The Yorkshire Vet
programme.desc: A heartwarming documentary series that follows the work of former Herriot Trainee Peter Wright and his partner. The show focuses on the declining veterinary specialism of small animals or livestock, and follows the pair of vets on visit to clients in remote farm locations as they care for animals in the rural communities of North Yorkshire. The show also benefits from the beautiful backgrounds and stunning scenery of the Yorkshire Dales and North York Moors, adding an extra dimension to this veterinary show.

programme.title: River Monsters
programme.desc: Extreme angler Jeremy Wade is on the hunt for freshwater fish with a taste for human flesh. This rip-roaring ride through the dark side of nature mixes action and adventure with mysteries, edge of the seat chase and a battle of wills between man and almost supernatural beasts. Jeremy illustrates to the viewers exactly how these river monsters are constructed to kill using forensic methods.

programme.title: Giants
programme.desc: Crocodiles. Dan O'Neill is on a mission to find, film and measure the biggest living crocodiles; he joins an indigenous saltwater crocodile guide in the hope of to tracking a giant male down.

programme.title: Giants
programme.desc: Dan O'Neill is on a mission to find the biggest living anaconda; he joins Dr Juliana Terra, an anaconda expert, in the hope of tracking a giant green anaconda female down.

programme.title: Ice Age: A Frozen World
programme.desc: Ice Age: A Frozen World is a factual thriller fronted by naturalist and explorer Steve Backshall and wildlife presenter Michaela Strachan. This three-part series takes viewers on a gripping journey into the heart of the Ice Age using stunning location filming from around the world, breath-taking Virtual Production and expert interviews. The series will unravel the hidden secrets of the Ice Age and how it created the world we now live in. The series chronicles the rise of the mega beasts, from woolly mammoths to sabre tooth cats; the David and Goliath story of Neanderthals versus Homo Sapiens and the ultimate irony that global warming could trigger the next Ice Age.

programme.title: Raptors
programme.desc: An insightful and spectacular celebration of birds of prey, our planet's most successful hunters; from frozen wilderness to tangled jungle, this episode reveals the raptors as never before.

programme.title: Gladiators
programme.desc: Witness clashes over precious resources when the dry season brings a band of gladiators to an African savannah watering hole. See a lion-elephant territory brawl, an ant raid on a termite mound, and a honey badger's risky dance with a deadly snake.

programme.desc: Cheetah's Burning Plains. Being thin, having black spots on whitish hair, hyperventilating and licking regularly to evaporate saliva are the cheetah's most efficient tricks for tolerating its fiery environment.

programme.title: Hot Life: Africa
programme.desc: Wild Dogs, Tough Territory. Most species that live in extreme places are delaying their life cycles of reproduction and breeding; wild dogs are advancing their biology by several weeks to avoid the dangers of heat to their pups.

programme.title: Massive Africa
programme.desc: Take a journey through the wild plains of Africa in this visually stunning documentary series, highlighting the vast continent's diverse wildlife and dramatic landscapes. We travel through varied, untamed regions, including Zambia's Luangwa Valley, the Namib desert, Mala-Mala game reserve and the Okavango Swamps, to film these magnificent creatures in their natural habitats. A breathtaking encapsulation of wildlife on Africa, we showcase the deadly predators that govern these lands and the teeming herds of prey they hunt.

programme.title: Outback Vet
programme.desc: Outback Vet is a documentary series following a vet hospital that never stops working. From cute family pets and their owners, to deadly whale sharks, wild and domestic animals on land and water in remote locations- Outback Vet has it all in the wild outback of Western Australia. The series follows Rick Fenny, the so-called 'Mad Max' of his profession, his vet daughter Louisa and marine scientist son Ed as they care for and protect animals of Western Australia.

programme.title: Wildest Survival
programme.desc: Dive into the breathtaking world of nature as we explore the lives of our planet's weirdest and wildest creatures, learning how they have adapted to their surroundings in order to survive. Some of these remarkable species have lived on our planet for thousands, if not millions, of years. We reveal how these animals have evolved through the generations to remain a thriving species. With the current, devastating environmental plight, Wildest Survival showcases the importance of these wonderful species, showing what we could lose if human habits remain unaltered.
